# SHL Assessment Recommendation System — Walkthrough

## What Was Built

A production-grade, end-to-end **AI-powered SHL Assessment Recommender** with:
- **Playwright web scraper** → 389 assessments from SHL catalog
- **ChromaDB + sentence-transformers** vector index
- **FastAPI** REST API (`/health` + `/recommend`)
- **Gemini 1.5 Flash** re-ranking (when API key is set)
- **Premium dark frontend** (zero frameworks, zero watermarks)
- **predictions.csv** with 90 rows (9 queries × 10 recommendations)

---

## Project Layout

```
SHL_Assessment_Recommender_System/
├── backend/
│   ├── main.py                 ← FastAPI app
│   ├── scraper.py              ← Playwright scraper
│   ├── embedder.py             ← ChromaDB + sentence-transformers
│   ├── recommender.py          ← Hybrid search + Gemini re-ranking
│   ├── evaluate.py             ← Recall@10 evaluation
│   ├── generate_predictions.py ← Generate predictions.csv
│   ├── requirements.txt
│   ├── Dockerfile
│   └── chroma_db/              ← Local vector store (auto-created)
├── frontend/
│   └── index.html              ← Full UI (single file)
└── data/
    ├── shl_catalog.json        ← 389 assessments
    └── predictions.csv         ← 91 rows (header + 90 predictions)
```

